			<head>Biographical Note</head>
			<p>Raised in Northern New York, attorney John Charles Harris graduated from Mount Union College, Alliance, Ohio.  As co-founder of the Houston and Galveston-based law firm Harris  Harris with Edward Harris, he litigated for Southwestern Telephone and Telegraph Company.  Often engaged as a public speaker, Harris’s 1907 address to the Texas Bar Association on legal ethics was published as a monograph.</p>
