			<head>Scope and Contents</head>
			<p>Comprising speeches and a letter, the John Charles Harris Papers, 1906-1909, document Harris’s career as an attorney and his community and social involvement.  The speeches relate to fraternity reunions, dedications, women’s suffrage, holidays, and eulogies.  The letter, addressed to Judge Charles E. Ashe, concerns Southwestern Telephone and Telegraph Company litigation.</p>
